# Drag PDF Privacy Policy

Last Updated: February 22, 2024

## Introduction

Thank you for using Drag PDF! This document outlines our commitment to your privacy and security. Drag PDF is an open-source application dedicated to providing a seamless PDF management experience without collecting any personal information from its users.

## Information Collection and Usage

Drag PDF **does not collect any personal information** from its users. We respect your privacy and have designed the application to operate without the need for user data.

## Security

We take the security of your information seriously. While Drag PDF does not handle personal data, we are committed to maintaining a secure environment for your PDF files. Any files processed by Drag PDF are treated with the utmost confidentiality, and we employ industry-standard security measures to protect against unauthorized access or disclosure.

## Third-Party Services

Drag PDF does not utilize any third-party services or APIs that might compromise your privacy. The application operates as a standalone tool, focusing solely on providing a reliable and secure PDF management experience.

## Data Storage

As part of our commitment to privacy, Drag PDF **does not store any user data** on external servers or cloud storage. All operations and file manipulations are performed locally on your device.

## Changes to this Privacy Policy

We may update this privacy policy occasionally to reflect changes in our practices or for legal and regulatory reasons. Users will be notified of any significant updates. It is recommended to review this policy periodically.

## Contact Us

If you have any questions or concerns regarding your privacy while using Drag PDF, please contact us at [keys.01yacht@icloud.com](mailto:keys.01yacht@icloud.com).

Your privacy is important to us, and we appreciate your trust in using Drag PDF.

Thank you for choosing Drag PDF!